<P>
South and North Korean officials met for nearly three hours but failed to make 
any progress toward setting up a meeting of their prime ministers because of 
differences over joint U.S.-South Korean military exercises. But they agreed to 
meet again April 12 at the truce village of Panmunjom, 35 miles north of Seoul. 
The north wants the annual exercises scrapped. 
</P>
