<TEXT>
<P>
Emergency legislation to provide $24.5 million to keep open 21 centers for the 
mentally retarded and developmentally disabled was signed by Gov. George 
Deukmejian. The funding crisis developed as a result of a dispute between the 
Deukmejian Administration and the federal government over funding of the 
centers. The legislation sponsored by Sen. John Seymour (R-Anaheim) provides 
that the Administration can use money from the state General Fund or borrow it 
from another state-controlled fund until there is a resolution of the dispute. 
</P>
