<HEADLINE>
<P>
DR. JOHN D. ABBEY, 74; HELPED FOUND DOWNEY COMMUNITY HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John D. Abbey, a physician and longtime member of the Los Angeles County 
Hospital Commission, has died in Downey Community Hospital, which he helped 
found at its present site in 1970. 
</P>
<P>
An ear, nose and throat specialist, Abbey, 74, was named to the county 
commission in 1975 by Supervisor Pete Schabarum. He also was a past president 
of Southeast District 10 of the Los Angeles county Medical Assn. 
</P>
<P>
Survivors include his wife, Genevieve, a son, daughter and three grandchildren. 
Services will be held today at 11:30 a.m. at First Presbyterian Church of 
Downey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
