<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEREDITARY RULERS PICK MALAYSIAN MONARCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nine hereditary rulers Thursday elected Sultan Azlan Muhibuddin Shah, a 
60-year-old former Supreme Court judge, as Malaysia's monarch for the next five 
years. 
</P>
<P>
After two days of deliberations at the national palace, the sultans in a secret 
ballot selected Azlan, the present deputy king, to ascend to the throne. He 
will take office in April, replacing King Mahmood Iskandar, 56, the sultan of 
the southern state of Johore, who took office in 1983. 
</P>
