<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-LAWMAKER IN HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Rep. James O'Hara (D-Mich.) was in critical condition Thursday at George 
Washington Hospital, where he was admitted recently suffering from lung cancer, 
a spokeswoman said. O'Hara, 65, represented Michigan's 12th District for 18 
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA030389-0057 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 25801 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 3, 1989, Friday, San Diego County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part 2; Page 1; Column 4; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
