<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 30-year-old man was in good condition after being shot early Thursday as he 
fled a burglary, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Edward Wilson was shot in the left arm after a burglary at the home of Joseph 
Schimka, 55, in the 5000 block of Hilda Road, police said. Schimka told police 
he heard sounds from the garage just before 3 a.m. When he went onto the porch, 
he saw a man carrying a vacuum cleaner and yelled for him to stop. 
</P>
<P>
The man dropped the vacuum cleaner and was running away when Schimka fired a 
shot from a .45-caliber semiautomatic, police said. When Schimka went to call 
police, he said, his wife saw a second man run from the garage. 
</P>
<P>
Wilson, who was taken to UC San Diego Medical Center to be treated for the 
wound, will be arrested in connection with burglary, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police found a truck about half a block away that contained Schimka's tools, 
food that was stored in a garage freezer and an electric floor buffer. 
</P>
<P>
The San Diego County district attorney's office will determine whether Schimka 
was justified in shooting, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
