<P>
 $2-MILLION BAIL SET FOR TODD BRIDGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles Municipal Judge David Horwitz set bail in the amount of $2 million 
Thursday for actor Todd Bridges, who is charged with the attempted murder of a 
man inside a reputed "rock house." 
</P>
<P>
Bridges, 23, the former child star of NBC-TV's "Diff'rent Strokes," had been 
held without bail since his arrest a month ago. 
</P>
<P>
Bridges remained in custody and faces a March 9 preliminary hearing. 
</P>
<P>
Bridges is also being held in an unrelated case in Compton in which he is 
charged with stealing his BMW automobile at gunpoint from a South Los Angeles 
repair man without paying a $500 bill. The alleged robbery occurred about two 
weeks before the shooting. 
</P>
