<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN PLEADS GUILTY TO MOLESTATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The former music director of classical radio station KUSC-FM has pleaded guilty 
to molesting an 8-year-old girl while posing as a physician and pretending to 
examine her for an infection. 
</P>
<P>
David Jay Letterman, 40, entering his guilty plea in Los Angeles Superior Court 
on Tuesday, was charged with one felony count of lewd conduct with a child 
under age 14. 
</P>
<P>
Letterman, who remains free, was scheduled to be sentenced April 4. 
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors said the molestation occurred after Letterman went to the victim's 
house and, posing as a doctor, asked her mother for permission to examine the 
child for an infection. 
</P>
<P>
A station spokesman said Letterman no longer works at KUSC. The spokesman was 
unsure whether Letterman was fired or had quit. 
</P>
