FIVE COUNTY SURFERS ADVANCE AT SANTA CRUZ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Noah Budroe of Huntington Beach and Jim Hogan of Capistrano Beach were among 
five Orange County surfers to advance Thursday in the Cold Water surfing 
tournament at Santa Cruz. 
</P>
<P>
Other Orange County surfers to advance were Dino Andino of San Clemente, Matt 
Archbold of Dana Point and Gary Clisby of Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
John Parmenter and Bud Llamas of Huntington Beach, who won their opening-round 
heats Wednesday, were eliminated Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The event, which continues through Sunday, is the first stop on the 1989 Assn. 
of Surfing Professionals world tour. 
