<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE COLLEGES; 
</P>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
UC IRVINE WOMEN LOSE TO LONG BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UC Irvine's women's basketball team played Cal State Long Beach tough for a 
half Thursday but the 49ers rallied for a 97-68 victory in a Big West 
Conference game at Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Cheryl Dowell, who finished with 18 points and 10 rebounds, scored the first 
four points of a 12-0 run to start the second half for Long Beach (24-4, 17-0), 
which has won 17 in a row. 
</P>
<P>
Penny Toler scored 21 points for Long Beach. Natasha Parks and Kathy Lizarraga 
scored 15 points each for Irvine, which was tied, 41-41, at the half. Parks had 
12 rebounds for Irvine (8-18, 4-13). 
</P>
<P>
In California Collegiate Athletic Ass, women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Northridge 89, Chapman 73 -- Host Chapman led, 39-38, at the half but 
was outscored in the second half, 51-34. Bridgette Ealy scored 23 points to 
lead Northridge. Julie King scored 16 for Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
In the National Christian College Division II men's national basketball 
championship tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Pacific Coast Christian 89, Pilsbery 73 -- Steve Heard and Steve Welch scored 
18 points to lead PCC (18-11) in the first-round game at Jimmy Swaggart Bible 
College in Baton Rouge, La. Brian Keiser added 14, Garrett Crayton 13 and Mike 
deVries 11 for PCC. 
</P>
<P>
In the National Christian College Athletic Assn. Division II women's basketball 
tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Pacific Coast Christian 76, Moody Bible (Chicago) 46 -- Kris Dodson scored 22 
points for lead Pacific Coast Christian in the first round of the Kentucky 
Christian College in Grayson, Ky. Angie Revert and Jody Pierce scored 14 points 
each, Gina Atkins 11 and Donna Allen 10 for PCC (18-11). 
</P>
</TEXT>
