<P>
Quiksilver Inc. reported that net income for the first quarter ended Jan. 31 
more than doubled to $822,000 from $380,000 in the comparable period last year. 
Net sales for the quarter rose 56% to $12.5 million from $8 million. 
Quiksilver, Costa Mesa, designs, arranges for the manufacture of, and 
distributes beachwear, ski wear and casual clothing primarily for young men and 
boys. 
