<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
GOETZ EARLY RELEASE PLEA DENIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ALBANY, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Subway gunman Bernhard Goetz, two months into a one-year jail sentence on an 
illegal gun possession conviction, was denied early release today by the state 
Board of Parole. 
</P>
<P>
A short statement issued by the board said releasing Goetz early "would 
deprecate the seriousness of the crime and undermine respect for the law." The 
board's decision means Goetz will likely have to serve his full one-year 
sentence, minus any time off for good behavior. Goetz began serving his 
sentence Jan. 13. He was convicted on the gun charge in connection with the 
Dec. 22, 1984, shooting of four black youths on a New York City subway train. 
Goetz is white. 
</P>
</TEXT>
