<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
GRANDSON BORN TO BRITAIN'S THATCHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DALLAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
British Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher became a grandmother this week with 
the birth of a boy to her daughter-in-law. 
</P>
<P>
Diane Thatcher, 28, wife of Mark Thatcher, the prime minister's 35-year-old 
son, had a normal delivery without complications Tuesday at Presbyterian 
Hospital of Dallas, hospital spokeswoman Ginger Seay said today. The healthy 
7-pound, 2-ounce baby, named Michael, and mother were released from the 
hospital Thursday, she said. 
</P>
<P>
An official at the British Embassy in Washington said "none of us here know of 
any plans for a visit" anytime soon by the prime minister. "If there were 
definite plans, we'd know." 
</P>
</TEXT>
