<DATELINE>
<P>
FAIRFAX, Va. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After being hospitalized following a one-car accident near Reston, Va., 
Clarence Vaughn, a three-year member of the Washington Redskins, was charged 
with driving while intoxicated and failure to obtain a Virginia driver's 
license, Fairfax County Police said. 
</P>
<P>
Vaughn was flown by helicopter to Fairfax Hospital after being freed from his 
car, which had struck a tree early this morning, said police spokeswoman Judy 
Duff. The 24-year-old defensive back didn't suffer any serious or 
life-threatening injuries, Duff said. 
